1. Edit target bench-pepc-*.xml file
   a. adapt number of nodes
   b. adapt number of particles, timesteps, etc.

2. to start the benchmark, use
   ./jube -start ##the edited xml file##
   e.g. ./jube -start bench-pepc-IBM-BGP-Jugene.xml

3. jube compiles and executes, have a tee or coffee, note the benchmark ID

4. to analyse the runs and show the results call
   ./jube -update -result -force ##benchmark ID##